cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.CE

The paper proposes a deep network framework for calculating virtual battery state from end-use measurements of an ensemble of flexible thermostatic loads. This involves transfer learning and the use of a stacked autoencoder. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
